ul.li:
fetches a GDK-Proton built from a WineGDK fork that implements XUser
          and request signing, so you sign in to Microsoft inside the game —
          no relay, no proxy;

with "Advanced diagnostics" enabled the game could hang or crash
              with broken menus — the verbose logging was flooding and starving
              the game; it now stays fast and playable with diagnostics on;

the game no longer freezes on the "Get Started" screen with the
              music still playing — the online-login component it needs is now
              published, so signing in completes instead of hanging;

fixes the crash when opening or closing Settings or pausing the
              game (seen mainly on the Steam Deck) by giving the game more
              stack room;

redesigned launcher with rounded, flat controls and crisp
              antialiased text — and it is fully self-contained, so it looks
              the same on every distribution with nothing to install;

fixes a crash on the first launch after install, caused by
              Proton's OpenXR runtime — VR is now fully disabled so the game
              starts straight into normal (flat) mode;

initialises the Wine prefix before installing the input and
              login components, fixing a "system32 not found" failure on a
              fresh install;
